This paper deals with representation learning and disentanglement for visual data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning model for cross-domain joint feature disentanglement and adaptation, which involves transfer learning and domain adaptation, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions classification tasks, which suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL).
